$ Android Studio: File -> Projekt Structure

The keyboard shortcut for *File -> Projekt Structure* is `ctrl+alt+shift+s`.

Projekt:
  • Android Gradle Plugin Version
  • Gradle Version

{ Android SDK Location

  The ~Android SDK Location~ allows to specify a location for projects without a `local.properties` file with an `sdk.dir` property

  The value of ~Android NDK Location~ will be safed as `ndk.dir` property in the `local.properties` file.

 ~JDK location~ specifies the → development/languages/Java#jdk[JDK] that Gradle uses when it builds a project

